    • Method Detail

      • decodeStatementKey

        public static IV[] decodeStatementKey(byte[] key,
                      int arity)
        Decode a key from one of the statement indices. The components of the key are returned in the order in which they appear in the key. The caller must reorder those components using their knowledge of which index is being decoded in order to reconstruct the corresponding RDF statement. The returned array will always have 4 components. However, the last key component will be null if there are only three components in the key.
        Parameters:
        key - The key.
        Returns:
        An ordered array of the IVs for that key.
